h3. Issue Summary

The number field in the customer portal is shown without a floating-point separator, different behavior from the issue view.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a custom field with the number field type;
 # Add this field to create/edit/view screens in a Service Desk project;
 # Open a request using this number field, for example, 123456789;
 # In the issue view the floating-point will appear, separating the numbers;
 # In the customer portal the number will show without the separator;

h3. Expected Results

The floating-point will appear in the number field when necessary.
h3. Actual Results

The floating-point doesn't appear, treating the field as text.
h3. Workaround

Currently, there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary

When creating an automation rule to send a Webhook with a custom payload with the variable {{$\{event.user.name}}}, the variable is not interpolated with any value and is sent empty.

-

This bug was reported in Community Questions, at the following question: [https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Jira-Service-Desk-questions/Automation-webhook-custom-payload-variables-missing/qaq-p/1408516]
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a custom automation rule, with:
 ## WHEN: "Issue resolution changed";
 ## THEN: "Webhook";
 ## Configure the webhook with a test URL;
 ## Select "Send custom payload" as body type;
 ## Add the following to the payload textarea:
 \{ "user" : "${event.user.name}" }
 ## Confirm;
 # Before saving the new rule, click in the "Options" link in the upper-right corner, and select "Run as the user who triggered the rule";
 # Save the new rule;
 # Add the webhook test URL to the Whitelist ([http://PATH_TO_JIRA/plugins/servlet/whitelist|http://path_to_jira/plugins/servlet/whitelist]);
 # Trigger the automation rule by resolving an issue.

h3. Expected Results

The webhook should be called with a value like:
{code:java}
{
  "user": "my_user_name"
}
{code}
h3. Actual Results

The webhook is called without a value for the user:
{code:java}
{
  "user": ""
}{code}
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Summary

When a user sets the language as Spanish and vendor calls on:

{noformat}
/rest/servicedeskapi/request/{issueKey}/approval
{noformat}

it returns an English version of the {{name}} and {{finalDecision}}:

{code}
{
    "id": "1",
    "name": "Waiting for approval",
    "finalDecision": "approved",
    "canAnswerApproval": false,
    "approvers": [
        {
            "approver": {
                "name": "admin",
                "key": "admin",
                "emailAddress": "...",
                "displayName": "...",
                "active": true,
                "timeZone": "Europe/Lisbon",
                "_links": {
                    "jiraRest": "http://localhost:8080/rest/api/2/user?username=admin",
                    "avatarUrls": {
                       ...
                    "self": "http://localhost:8080/rest/api/2/user?username=admin"
                }
            },
            "approverDecision": "approved"
        }
    ],
    "createdDate": {
        "iso8601": "2018-11-12T10:40:45+0000",
        "jira": "2018-11-12T10:40:45.961+0000",
        "friendly": "Hace 17 minutos",
        "epochMillis": 1542019245961
    },
    "completedDate": {
        "iso8601": "2018-11-12T10:41:25+0000",
        "jira": "2018-11-12T10:41:25.996+0000",
        "friendly": "Hace 16 minutos",
        "epochMillis": 1542019285996
    },
    "_links": {
        "self": "http://localhost:8080/rest/servicedeskapi/request/10302/approval/1"
    }
}
{code}

Expected Output: Should be in Spanish as well

h3. Investigation

As per [Translating resolutions, priorities, statuses, and issue types|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver073/translating-resolutions-priorities-statuses-and-issue-types-861253259.html], the status can be customized. REST API {{/rest/api/2/issue/<issueIdOrKey>}} respects this and returns proper translation of the status, but {{/rest/servicedeskapi/request/<issueKey>/approval}} does not. 

However, when renaming the status/transition in Jira Settings -> Workflows , then it reflects the changes for the {{name}} of the status/transition, which boils down to what the hierarchy of the requirement is, to use name provided in the workflow vs the custom translation
